  "title": "Senior Portfolio Manager (Urgent/Investment/SME/S$18,000 higher)",
  "description": "<p><strong>* Basic Up to S$18,000 </strong><br /><strong>\n* Work Life Balance & Friendly Environment</strong><br /><strong>\n* Incentive Scheme & Career development</strong><br /><strong>\n* Candidate with Minimum 15 Year experience in Investment Finance Industry</strong><br /><strong>\n* Responsible for the P&L, Sales and Operations for the Service\nDivision</strong></p><p>Our company is looking\nfor suitable candidates to join their growing business as <strong>Senior</strong> <strong>Portfolio Manager</strong>.</p><p><strong>RESPONSIBILITIES:</strong></p><p>·       Managed investments for single family office</p><p>·       Research various fund structures and\nalternative investments</p><p>·       Prepare market and monthly performance reports\nfor investors</p><p>·       Conduct quantitative and qualitative analysis\non investment opportunities and prepare investment reports for decision-making\npurposes</p><p>·       Perform due diligence, lead investments\nnegotiations, and coordinate legal aspects</p><p>·       Review business performance, recommend changes\nto the existing investment portfolios</p><p>·       Identify potential strategic investment</p><p>·       Lead the investment strategy and associated\nactivities</p><p><strong>REQUIREMENT:</strong></p><p>·       MAS Representative would be highly\nadvantageous</p><p>·       Master's/Bachelor's Degree in a quantitative\ndiscipline (Finance, Economics, Mathematics, or similar), with CFA preferred</p><p>·       Preferable at least 15 years of relevant\nworking experience in the stock exchange (US & HK market) or public equity\ninvestment background</p><p>·       Strong quantitative and financial modelling\nbackground with hands on experience on building tactical asset allocation\nmodels</p><p>·       Strong communication skills (English &\nChinese) to liaise with Chinese-speaking director(s)<br /></p><p>\n<strong>OTHER INFORMATION:</strong><br />\n• Location : One Fullerton (Near Raffle MRT)</p><p>• Working hours :\n9.00am to 6.00pm (5 Days)<br />\n• Salary: up to S$18,000 higher/ Negotiable (Salary will commensurate according\nto experience & qualifications)</p><p><strong>HOW TO APPLY:</strong></p><p>Interested candidate,\nplease submit your updated resume in MS WORD Format to:</p><p>Email – johnson@jyj.com.sg</p><p>We regret to inform\nyou that only shortlisted candidates will be notified. All applications will be\ntreated with the strictest confidence.</p>",
